t%20for%20about%2010%2C000%20years.%20Radiocarbon%20dating%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blm.gov%2Fpress-release%2Ftesting-yields-new-evidence-human-occupation-18000-years-ago-oregon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevealed%20the%3C%2Fa%3E%20tooth%20enamel%20to%20be%2018%2C250%20years%20old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20they%20know%20how%20old%20the%20teeth%20are%2C%20O'Grady%20and%20the%20team%20plan%20to%20publish%20the%20findings%20in%20a%20peer-reviewed%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20tools%20were%20below%20the%20teeth%2C%20the%20researchers%20estimate%20they're%20at%20least%20as%20old%2C%20or%20older%2C%20than%20the%2018%2C250-year-old%20teeth.%20It's%20basically%20like%20if%20you%20were%20to%20try%20and%20date%20the%20laundry%20in%20your%20laundry%20basket%20for%20the%20week%2C%20O'Grady%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clothes%20you%20tossed%20in%20on%20Monday%20will%20sit%20below%20whatever%20you%20tossed%20in%20on%20Thursday%2C%20as%20long%20as%20no%20one's%20dug%20through%20it%20already%20(or%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20archaeological%20finds%2C%20as%20long%20as%20there%20wasn't%20a%20geological%20shakeup.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20Stone%20Age%20Swiss%20Army%20knife%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20tools%20are%20made%20of%20orange%20chalcedony%2C%20a%20type%20of%20quartz.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20really%20high-quality%20tool%20stone%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20away%2C%20O'Grady%20and%20his%20colleagues%20were%20surprised%20to%20find%20that%20type%20of%20stone.%20%26quot%3BIt%20didn't%20look%20familiar%20to%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20They%20determined%20the%20stone's%20place%20of%20origin%20was%20at%20least%2050%20to%2075%20miles%20away.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Several%20people%20stand%20near%20the%20Rimrock%20Draw%20Rockshelter%2C%20an%20archeological%20site%20containg%20stone%20tools%20that%20are%20over%2018%2C000%20years%20old%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6513363051acc80019f0da93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArtist-in-residence%20Nancy%20Pobanz%20gives%20a%20presentation%20at%20the%20Rimrock%20Draw%20Rockshelter%20archeological%20site.%3Cp%3EPatrick%20O'Grady%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tool%20they%20found%20in%202012%20is%20a%20bit%20smaller%20than%20the%20size%20of%20a%20wallet%20with%20a%20rounded%2C%20rectangular%20shape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20had%20three%20edges%20that%20had%20different%20kinds%20of%20flaking%20done%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said%2C%20a%20curved%20blade%2C%20a%20flatter%20side%2C%20and%20sawtooth%20edge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20easily%20hold%20the%20thing%20and%20use%20all%20three%20of%20those%20different%20functioning%20edges%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said%2C%20like%20a%20multi-purpose%20tool%20or%20Swiss%20Army%20knife.%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20tool%20is%20also%20orange%20chalcedony%20and%20is%20about%203%20inches%20long%20and%20appears%20to%20be%20only%20lightly%20used.%20It%20may%20be%20a%20chipped-off%20piece%20of%20another%20tool.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBison%20blood%20and%20camel%20teeth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20tested%20the%20multi-tool%20and%20found%20bison%20blood%20on%20it.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmnch.uoregon.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-02%2FRDR%2520Synopsis.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENewer%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20researchers%20found%20at%20the%20site%20contained%20remnants%20of%20mountain%20sheep%20and%20horse%20blood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20blood%20and%20many%20camel%20and%20bison%20teeth%20fragments%20suggest%20people%20used%20the%20site%20as%20a%20place%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F300000-year-old-schoeningen-marking-early-prehistoric-clothing-bear-skin-2023-1%5C%22%3Ebutcher%20animals%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20as%20a%20full-time%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20camp%20that%20people%20came%20to%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20and%20especially%20when%20they%20were%20hunting%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221130%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tooth%20enamel%20from%20a%20camelops%2C%20an%20ancient%20camel%20ancestor%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6513379851acc80019f0daec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22846%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20of%20the%20tooth%20enamel%20found%20at%20the%20Rimrock%20Draw%20Rockshelter%20is%20over%2018%2C000%20years%20old.%3Cp%3EThomas%20W.%20Stafford%2C%20Jr.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rimrock%20Draw%20Rockshelter%2C%20where%20the%20tools%20were%20found%2C%20is%20a%2065-foot%20cleft%20in%20a%20basalt%20rim%20near%20an%20ancient%2C%20now-dry%20stream.%20There%20could%20be%20more-permanent%20dwellings%20in%20the%20area%20archaeologists%20have%20yet%20to%20find.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20oldest%20evidence%20of%20humans%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20experts%20believed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-in-north-america-15000-years-earlier-than-archaeologists-thought-2020-7%5C%22%3EClovis%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20the%20first%20humans%20in%20North%20America%2C%20having%20crossed%20the%20Bering%20land%20bridge%20from%20Siberia%20to%20Canada%2013%2C000%20years%20ago.%20But%20recent%20discoveries%20have%20indicated%20a%20pre-Clovis%20culture%20that's%20thousands%20of%20years%20older.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOregon%20and%20surrounding%20states%20contain%20some%20of%20the%20oldest%20evidence%20of%20ancient%20human%20habitation%20in%20the%20US.%20Coopers%20Ferry%2C%20in%20Idaho%2C%20is%20about%20240%20miles%20to%20the%20northeast%20of%20Rimr