ity%20payments%20will%20continue%20to%20go%20out%20should%20the%20government%20shut%20down%20%E2%80%94%20but%20don't%20expect%20to%20get%20help%20if%20you%20need%20a%20new%20card%2C%20or%20are%20dealing%20with%20overpayment%20issues.%20The%20agency's%20contingency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fagency%2Fshutdown%2Fmaterials%2Fcontingency-plan-08-14-23.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eplan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20that%208%2C500%20employees%20will%20be%20furloughed%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20shutdown%2C%20with%2053%2C000%20exempted%20from%20shutdown%20furloughs.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENancy%20Altman%2C%20the%20president%20of%20advocacy%20group%20Social%20Security%20Works%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F26%2Fpolitics%2Fsenior-social-security-government-shutdown%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20shutdown%20could%20potentially%20lead%20to%20further%20slowdowns%20for%20various%20customer%20service%2C%20as%20workers%20leave%20rather%20than%20forego%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20shutdown%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20more%20difficult%20for%20Americans%20receiving%20food%20assistance.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20warned%20a%20shutdown%20could%20mean%20that%20low-income%20mothers%20and%20children%20might%20find%20themselves%20without%20aid%20from%20the%20Special%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Program%20for%20Women%2C%20Infants%2C%20and%20Children%2C%20commonly%20known%20as%20WIC.%20Without%20additional%20funding%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F09%2F25%2Fextreme-house-republicans-chaos-is-marching-america-toward-a-shutdown-that-would-jeopardize-vital-nutrition-assistance-for-nearly-7-million-vulnerable-moms-and-young-children%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWhite%20House%20said%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nearly%207%20million%20mothers%20and%20children%20could%20risk%20losing%20that%20assistance%20as%20states%20are%20forced%20to%20make%20waiting%20lists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecretary%20of%20Agriculture%20Tom%20Vilsack%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fpress-briefings%2F2023%2F09%2F25%2Fpress-briefing-by-press-secretary-karine-jean-pierre-and-secretary-of-agriculture-tom-vilsack%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebriefing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20SNAP%2C%20the%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Assistance%20Program%20commonly%20known%20as%20food%20stamps%2C%20would%20continue%20for%20at%20least%20the%20month%20of%20October%20should%20there%20be%20a%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20shutdown%20were%20to%20extend%20longer%20than%20that%2C%20there%20would%20be%20some%20serious%20consequences%20to%20SNAP%2C%26quot%3B%20Vilsack%20said.%20For%20WIC%2C%20the%20impacts%20will%20be%20more%20immediate%20and%20dire%3A%20Vilsack%20said%20that%20USDA%20has%20a%20contingency%20fund%20that%20could%20keep%20the%20program%20afloat%20for%20%26quot%3Ba%20day%20or%20two.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20vast%20majority%20of%20WIC%20participants%20would%20see%20an%20immediate%20reduction%20and%20elimination%20of%20those%20benefits%2C%20which%20means%20the%20nutrition%20assistance%20that's%20provided%20would%20not%20be%20available.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Office%20of%20Management%20and%20Budget%20has%20instructed%20all%20federal%20agencies%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fomb%2Finformation-for-agencies%2Fagency-contingency-plans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eprepare%20contingency%20plans%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20shutdown%2C%20and%20it's%20looking%20increasingly%20likely%20those%20plans%20will%20soon%20have%20to%20be%20employed.%20With%20just%20a%20handful%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edays%20until%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20lawmaker