%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695758059000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65132f6051acc80019f0d8e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-shutdown-2023-will-social-security-be-paid-snap-benefits-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20federal%20government%20shutdown%20will%20happen%20Saturday%20if%20Congress%20doesn't%20agree%20on%20funding%20by%20then.%20It%20could%20risk%20benefits%20Americans%20rely%20on.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey%2CJuliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A28%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-shutdown-2023-will-social-security-be-paid-snap-benefits-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US-made%20ATACMS%20cluster%20missiles%20could%20give%20Ukraine's%20HIMARS%20the%20power%20to%20punish%20Russia's%20artillery%20and%20'cut%20off'%20its%20army%2C%20former%20US%20artillery%20officer%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222647%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Army%20Tactical%20Missile%20System.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6512d3351c099d0019acfd5d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221323%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20MGM-140%20Army%20Tactical%20Missile%20System.%3Cp%3EUS%20military%20photo%20by%20John%20Hamilton%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EWashington%20will%20send%20Ukraine%20much-sought-after%20ATACMS%2C%20tactical%20long-range%20missiles%2C%20according%20to%20multiple%20reports.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EOne%20variant%20that%20could%20help%20Kyiv%20is%20the%20M39%20cluster%20missile%2C%20which%20has%20nearly%201%2C000%20submunitions.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EA%20former%20US%20artillery%20officer%20says%20these%20weapons%20can%20hammer%20Russian%20artillery%20and%20isolate%20portions%20of%20its%20army.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20forces%20are%20increasingly%20using%20long-range%20cruise%20missiles%20to%20pound%20high-value%20Russian%20positions%20far%20behind%20the%20war's%20front%20lines.%20It%20has%20only%20a%20limited%20supply%20of%20these%20weapons%2C%20but%20Kyiv%20has%20its%20eyes%20set%20on%20the%20US-provided%20MGM-140%20Army%20Tactical%20Missile%20System%20(ATACMS)%20to%20help%20it%20keep%20up%20the%20pressure%20on%20high-value%20targets%20in%20the%20rear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20hasn't%20yet%20been%20announced%2C%20but%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20agreed%20to%20send%20ATACMS%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20according%20to%20multiple%20reports.%20The%20exact%20variant%20Kyiv's%20forces%20might%20receive%20is%2C%20however%2C%20unclear.%20A%20former%20US%20artillery%20officer%20says%20the%20M39%2C%20an%20older%20but%20still%20deadly%20long-range%20cluster%20missile%20packed%20with%20hundreds%20of%20explosive%20submunitions%2C%20is%20a%20likely%20choice%20and%20could%20allow%20Ukraine%20to%20isolate%20the%20Russian%20army%20on%20the%20occupied%20Crimean%20peninsula%20and%20hammer%20its%20artillery%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20without%20having%20to%20liberate%20more%20territory%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20take%20the%20ground%20to%20prevent%20the%20Russians%20from%20being%20able%20to%20use%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Dan%20Rice%2C%20who%20previously%20served%20as%20a%20special%20advisor%20to%20Ukraine's%20military%20leadership%2C%20told%20Insider.%20Rice%20has%20lobbied%20for%20Washington%20to%20send%20cluster%20munitions%20since%20July%202022%2C%20and%20his%20efforts%20have%20also%20focused%20on%20cluster%20rockets%20and%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20officials%2C%20US%20lawmakers%20in%20Congress%2C%20and%20experts%20and%20former%20US%20military%20officers%20have%20long%20pressured%20Washington%20to%20send%20ATACMS%2C%20missiles%20which%20can%20be%20fired%20from%20Kyiv's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatacms-gray-eagle-drones-kyiv-hit-russian-targets-inside-ukraine-2023-7%5C%22%3Eexisting%20arsenal%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US-provided%20High%20Mobility%20Artillery%20Rocket%20System%20(HIMARS)%2C%20but%20requests%20have%20been%20repeatedly%20met%20with%20reluctance%20from%20the%20White%20House%2C%20which%20has%20been%20concerned%20about%20both%20escalating%20the%20war%20and%20also%20straining%20its%20own%20stockpiles%20for%20this%20weapon.%20Last%20week%2C%20however%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20appeared%20to%20reverse%20course%20and%20told%20his%20counterpart%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20that%20he's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Fbiden-told-zelensky-u-s-is-willing-to-provide-long-range-atacms-missiles-3d125ab3%5C%22%3Ewilling%20to%20provide%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20missiles.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertain%20variants%20of%20the%20ground-launched%20ATACMS%2C%20like%20the%20M57s%20with%20their%20500-pound%20unitary%20warhead%2C%20can%20strike%20targets%20as%20far%20as%20186%20miles%20away%2C%20surpassing%20the%20155-mile%20range%20of%20the%20Western-made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-adapted-himars-ukraine-storm-shadow-missiles-bring-fear-back-2023-5%5C%22%3EStorm%20Shadow%2FSCALP-EG%3C%2Fa%3E%20air-launched%20cruise%20missiles%20that%20Ukraine%20received%20from%20the%20UK%20and%20France.%20Fewer%20of%20these%20were%20produced%20compared%20to%20the%20older%20M39%20cluster%20variant%2C%20military%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mca-marines.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F0518-Long-Range-Precision-Fires.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasc.army.mil%2Fweb%2Fportfolio-item%2Fatacms%2F%5C%22%3EM39%20ATACMS%20variant%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20saw%20use%20in%20Desert%20Storm%20and%20Operation%20Iraqi%20Freedom%2C%20only%20has%20a%20maximum%20range%20of%20around%20100%20miles%2C%20but%20that%20is%20still%20double%20the%20range%20of%20the%20precision%20Guided%20Multiple%20Launch%20Rocket%20System%20Ukraine%20is%20currently%20firing%20from%20its%20HIMARS.%20The%20M39%20is%20also%20packed%20with%20950%20anti-personnel%20and%20anti-materiel%20(APAM)%20M74%20bomblets.%20The%20submunitions%20are%20released%20and%20dispersed%20mid-flight%20over%20an%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Army%20Tactical%20Missile%20System%20(ATACMS)%20firing%20a%20missile%20into%20the%20East%20Sea%20during%20a%20South%20Korea-U.S.%20joint%20missile%20drill.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6512fe441c099d0019ad0770%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221705%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Army%20Tactical%20Missile%20System%20(ATACMS)%20firing%20a%20missile%20into%20the%20East%20Sea%20during%20a%20South%20Korea-U.S.%20joint%20missile%20drill.%3Cp%3ESouth%20Korean%20Defense%20Ministry%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERice%20told%20Insider%20on%20Monday%20that%20the%20transfer%20of%20the%20M39%20variant%20to%20Ukraine%20could%20come%20soon%20and%20alongside%20two%20other%20weapons%3A%20M26%20and%20M26A1%20cluster%20rockets.%20A%20Department%20of%20Defense%20official%20said%20Tuesday%20they%20were%20unable%20to%20confirm%20reports%20of%20what%20Biden%20and%20Zelenskyy%20discussed%20during%20their%20meeting%20last%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Biden%20has%20said%20in%20the%20past%20that%20ATACMS%20are%20not%20off%20the%20table%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20have%20anything%20new%20to%20announce%2C%26quot%3B%20Maj.%20Charlie%20Dietz%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20shared%20with%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20continue%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20we%20can%20do%20to%20help%20Ukraine%20succeed%20on%20the%20battlefield%20and%20protect%20its%20people.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20separate%20response%2C%20the%20State%20Department%20reiterated%20the%20Pentagon's%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIsolating%20the%20Russian%20army%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20M39%20missiles%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-himars-cluster-rocket-boost-former-us-artillery-officer-2023-8%5C%22%3EM26%20and%20M26A1%20cluster%20rockets%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20also%20be%20fired%20from%20Ukraine's%20HIMARS%2C%20combat-proven%20systems%20that%20have%20been%20a%20game-changer%20in%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20M26%20has%20a%20range%20of%20around%2018%20miles%20and%20is%20packed%20with%20around%20650%20submunitions%20while%20the%20M26A1%20variant%20has%20a%20range%20of%20around%2028%20miles%20and%20is%20packed%20with%20around%20510%20submunitions.%20These%20rockets%20are%20a%20step%20up%20from%20the%20155mm%20shells%20called%20dual-purpose%20improved%20conventional%20munitions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcluster-bombs-help-sustain-ukraine-strained-artillery-duels-russia-experts-2023-7%5C%22%3E(DPICMs)%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20US%20first%20delivered%20several%20months%20ago%20to%20Ukraine.%20Fired%20from%20shorter-range%20howitzer%20cannons%2C%20like%20the%20US-made%20M777%2C%20these%20shells%20have%20been%20a%20headache%20for%20Russian%20forces%2C%20and%20Rice%20previously%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20cluster%20rockets%20will%20only%20make%20things%20worse%20for%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20battlefield%2C%20Rice%20said%20the%20M39%20ATACMS%2C%20though%20likely%20not%20as%20good%20at%20striking%20facilities%20as%20newer%20missiles%2C%20will%20have%20two%20major%20impacts%3A%20the%20first%20is%20that%20Ukraine%20can%20cut%20off%20the%20Russian%20military%20in%20Crimea%20by%20denying%20it%20the%20ability%20to%20stay%20supplied%2C%20and%20the%20second%20is%20that%20Kyiv%20can%20wreak%20havoc%20on%20and%20further%20degrade%20Moscow's%20artillery%2C%20something%20cluster%20rockets%20can%20also%20do.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224942%5C%22