ut%2014%25%20smaller%20than%20supermoons%2C%20and%20sometimes%20seem%20dimmer%2C%20since%20the%20area%20illuminated%20by%20the%20sun%20appears%2030%25%20smaller%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timeanddate.com%2Fastronomy%2Fmoon%2Fmicro-moon.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETimeandDate.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20International%20Astronomical%20Union%20has%20not%20officially%20defined%20supermoons%20or%20micromoons%2C%20astronomers%20disagree%20on%20which%20full%20moons%20get%20the%20designation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20next%20full%20supermoon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20August%2019%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20next%20full%20micromoon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20February%2024%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBlue%20moons%20are%20like%20special%20bonuses.%20They%20occur%20every%20two%20or%20three%20years%2C%20when%20a%20month%20or%20season%20has%20one%20extra%20full%20moon.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20full%20moon%20rises%20over%20the%20Wyoming%20wilderness%20at%20Yellowstone%20National%20Park%2C%20making%20the%20sky%20look%20purple%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6513261d51acc80019f0d62a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20full%20moon%20isn't%20the%20best%20time%20to%20see%20stars%2C%20even%20at%20a%20place%20as%20dark%20as%20Yellowstone%20National%20Park.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lichtenstein%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20astronomical%20season%20(the%20time%20between%20solstice%20and%20equinox)%20has%20four%20full%20moons%20instead%20of%20the%20normal%20three%2C%20the%20third%20one%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timeanddate.com%2Fastronomy%2Fmoon%2Fblue-moon.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseasonal%20blue%20moon%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20calendar%20month%20has%20two%20full%20moons%2C%20the%20second%20one%20is%20a%20monthly%20blue%20moon.%20That%20happens%20because%20the%20lunar%20month%20is%20only%2029%20days%20long%2C%20while%20the%20Gregorian%20calendar%20month%20is%20usually%2030%20or%2031%20days%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20moon%20doesn't%20actually%20appear%20blue%20on%20these%20occasions.%20That%20would%20only%20happen%20if%20dust%20or%20smoke%20particles%20of%20a%20particular%20size%20cloud%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20say%20after%20a%20forest%20fire%2C%20volcanic%20eruption%2C%20or%20dust%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20next%20seasonal%20blue%20moon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20August%2019%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20next%20monthly%20blue%20moon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20August%2019%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffull-moon-names-meaning-origin-lunar-calendar-2023%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695756946000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651326f01c099d0019ad126a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffull-moon-names-meaning-origin-lunar-calendar-2023%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20full%20moon%20goes%20by%20many%20names%20each%20month%2C%20like%20the%20worm%20moon%20in%20March%20or%20the%20harvest%20moon%20in%20September%2C%20which%20originated%20to%20help%20track%20the%20seasons.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmcfalljohnsen%40insider.com%20(Morgan%20McFall-Johnsen%2CJenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffull-moon-names-meaning-origin-lunar-calendar-2023%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Want%20to%20move%20from%20side%20hustle%20to%20startup%3F%20Ditch%20your%20backup%20plan%2C%20says%20investor%20and%20guest%20'Shark%20Tank'%20shark%20Matt%20Higgins%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure