's%20most%20used%20airline%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20the%20most%20affected%2C%20the%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness-66917138%5C%22%3E%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJohan%20Lundgren%2C%20the%20chief%20executive%20of%20easyJet%2C%20said%2C%20''While%20it%20is%20regrettable%20that%20a%20temporary%20limit%20on%20capacity%20at%20Gatwick%20airport%20is%20required%2C%20we%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20the%20right%20action%20by%20the%20airport%20so%20on-the-day%20cancellations%20and%20delays%20can%20be%20avoided.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E''Gatwick%20airport%20and%20Nats%20now%20need%20to%20work%20on%20a%20longer-term%20plan%20so%20the%20resilience%20of%20%5Bair%20traffic%20control%5D%20at%20Gatwick%20is%20improved%20and%20fit%20for%20purpose.%20Our%20call%20for%20a%20more%20wide-ranging%20review%20of%20Nats%20remains%20so%20the%20broader%20issues%20can%20be%20examined%20so%20it%20can%20deliver%20robust%20services%20to%20passengers%20now%20and%20in%20the%20future.''%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-t%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bn%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BblueLinks%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695751920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fo9390kio_-gatwick-airport_625x300_26_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flondons-gatwick-airport-limits-flights-as-covid-19-outbreak-causes-staff-shortages-4426770%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20largest%20number%20of%20cancellations%20will%20be%20on%20Friday%2C%20September%2029%2C%20with%2033%20departures%20affected.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flondons-gatwick-airport-limits-flights-as-covid-19-outbreak-causes-staff-shortages-4426770%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flondons-gatwick-airport-limits-flights-as-covid-19-outbreak-causes-staff-shortages-4426770%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flondons-gatwick-airport-limits-flights-as-covid-19-outbreak-causes-staff-shortages-4426770%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Disease%20X%3A%20What%20Do%20We%20Know%3F%20Not%20Much%2C%20And%20That%20Is%20The%20Problem%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20UK%20health%20expert's%20warning%20that%20a%20new%20pathogen%20could%20cause%20a%20pandemic%20as%20deadly%20as%20the%20Spanish%20Flu%20-%20which%20killed%2050%20million%20people%20-%20has%20sent%20alarm%20bells%20ringing%20in%20a%20world%20that%20is%20yet%20to%20completely%20emerge%20from%20what%20it%20hoped%20was%20a%20once-in-a-lifetime%20event%20--%20Covid-19%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEsteemed%20Company%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cbr%3E%20Disease%20X%20is%20on%20the%20list%20of%20%26quot%3Bpriority%20diseases%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20WHO%20website%2C%20a%20roll%20call%20that%20also%20includes%20the%20Ebola%20virus%20disease%2C%20Middle%20East%20respiratory%20syndrome%20(MERS)%20and%20Severe%20Acute%20Respiratory%20Syndrome%20(SARS)%2C%20Nipah%20and%20Zika.%20These%20are%20all%20diseases%20that%20have%20a%20high%20fatality%20rate.%20The%20list%20was%20first%20published%20in%202017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Is%20Disease%20X%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20WHO%20website%2C%20Disease%20X%20%26quot%3Brepresents%20the%20knowledge%20that%20a%20serious%20international%20epidemic%20could%20be%20caused%20by%20a%20pathogen%20currently%20unknown%20to%20cause%20human%20disease%26quot%3B.%20The%20pathogen%20could%20be%20a%20virus%2C%20a%20bacterium%20or%20a%20fungus.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20essence%20then%2C%20it%20serves%20as%20a%20warning%20that%20the%20next%20pandemic%20could%20be%20lurking%20around%20the%20corner%20and%20it%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20predict%20what%20could%20cause%20it.%20It%20also%20helps%20direct%20research%20and%20investment%20towards%20emerging%20diseases%20and%20is%20meant%20to%20aid%20in%20the%20quick%20development%20of%20vaccines.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTargeting%20priority%20pathogens%20and%20virus%20families%20for%20research%20and%20development%20of%20countermeasures%20is%20essential%20for%20a%20fast%20and%20effective%20epidemic%20and%20pandemic%20response.%20Without%20significant%20R%26amp%3BD%20investments%20prior%20to%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%2C%20it%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20to%20have%20safe%20and%20effective%20vaccines%20developed%20in%20record%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20release%20quoted%20Dr%20Michael%20Ryan%2C%20Executive%20Director%20of%20WHO's%20Health%20Emergencies%20Programme%2C%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20The%20Expert%20Said%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fdebate%2Farticle-12551251%2Fpandemic-disease-x-covid.html%5C%22%3EDaily%20Mail%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Kate%20Bingham%2C%20who%20served%20as%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20UK's%20Vaccine%20Taskforce%20from%20May%20to%20December%202020%2C%20said%20the%20new%20virus%20could%20have%20a%20similar%20impact%20to%20the%20devastating%20Spanish%20Flu%20of%201919-1920.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%26quot%3BLet%20me%20put%20it%20this%20way%3A%20the%201918-19%20flu%20pandemic%20killed%20at%20least%2050%20million%20people%20worldwide%2C%20twice%20as%20many%20as%20were%20killed%20in%20World%20War%20I.%20Today%2C%20we%20could%20expect%20a%20similar%20death%20toll%20from%20one%20of%20the%20many%20viruses%20that%20already%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20sense%2C%20we%20got%20lucky%20with%20Covid-19%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20caused%2020%20million%20or%20more%20deaths%20across%20the%20world.%20The%20point%20is%20that%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20people%20infected%20with%20the%20virus%20managed%20to%20recover...%20Imagine%20Disease%20X%20is%20as%20infectious%20as%20measles%20with%20the%20fatality%20rate%20of%20Ebola.%20Somewhere%20in%20the%20world%2C%20it's%20replicating%2C%20and%20sooner%20or%20later%2C%20somebody%20will%20start%20feeling%20sick%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Bingham%20told%20the%20Daily%20Mail.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrategy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO's%20R%26amp%3BD%20Blueprint%20is%20a%20global%20strategy%20and%20preparedness%20plan%20that%20allows%20the%20rapid%20activation%20of%20research%20and%20development%20activities%20during%20epidemics.%20It%20is%20meant%20to%20to%20fast-track%20the%20availability%20of%20effective%20tests%2C%20vaccines%20and%20medicines%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20save%20lives%20and%20avert%20large-scale%20crises%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WHO%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20disease%20an%20R%26amp%3BD%20roadmap%20is%20created%2C%20followed%20by%20target%20product%20profiles.%20The%20roadmap%20is%20then%20used%20to%20guide%20the%20response%20to%20outbreaks%20in%20both%20urgent%20action%20and%20in%20developing%20ways%20to%20improve%20the%20global%20response%20for%20future%20epidemics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPandemics%20Increasing%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20origins%20of%20Covid-19%20aren't%20100%25%20clear%2C%20it%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20zoonotic%20disease%20which%20first%20infected%20a%20human%20in%20Wuhan%2C%20China%2C%20through%20a%20bat%20or%20some%20other%20animal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20National%20Center%20for%20Biotechnology%20Information%20(NCBI)%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20diseases%20to%20spread%20and%20escalate%20into%20epidemics%20or%20pandemics%20is%20increasing.%20The%20reasons%20cited%20for%20this%20include%20globalisation%20and%20the%20increased%20flow%20of%20humans%20and%20goods%20to%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20reasons%20include%20urbanisation%20and%20the%20fact%20that%2C%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20people%20are%20clustered%20together%20and%20living%20in%20overcrowded%20and%20unhygienic%20environments%20in%20which%20infectious%20diseases%20can%20thrive.%20The%20destruction%20of%20forests%20is%20also%20seen%20as%20a%20big%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20NCBI%20cites%20climate%20change%2C%20increased%20human-animal%20contact%2C%20and%20a%20shortage%20of%20health%20workers%20as%20the%20other%20reasons.%20The%20last%20of%20these%20is%20important%20because%20trained%20health%20workers%20can%20help%20identify%20and%20contain%20diseases%20before%20they%20spread%2C%20but%20they%20are%20usually%20lacking%20in%20places%20where%20such%20epidemics%20originate.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695751800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Ftrsj4j7g_disease-x_625x300_26_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdisease-x-what-do-we-know-not-much-and-that-is-the-problem-4426836%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20UK%20health%20expert's%20warning%20that%20a%20new%20pathogen%20could%20cause%20a%20pandemic%20as%20deadly%20as%20the%20Spanish%20Flu%20has%20sent%20alarm%20bells%20ringing%20in%20a%20world%20that%20is%20yet%20to%20completely%20emerge%20from%20what%20it%20hoped%20was%20a%20once-in-a-lifetime%20event%20--%20Covid-19%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdisease-x-what-do-we-know-not-much-and-that-is-the-problem-4426836%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdisease-x-what-do-we-know-not-much-and-that-is-the-problem-4426836%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdisease-x-what-do-we-know-not-much-and-that-is-the-problem-4426836%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22England%20will%20oppose%20playing%20Russian%20sides%20after%20UEFA%20lifts%20blanket%20ban%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695751500000%2C%22visual%