these%20slurs%2C%20but%20also%20the%20mindset%20of%20two%20members%20of%20his%20party%3B%20a%20party%20that%20owes%20much%20of%20its%20success%20to%20fostering%20anti-minority%20sentiments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20404px)%2085vw%2C%20404px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24141857%2FScreenshot-2023-09-24-at-2.17.38-PM-300x164.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22404%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24141857%2FScreenshot-2023-09-24-at-2.17.38-PM-300x164.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24141857%2FScreenshot-2023-09-24-at-2.17.38-PM.png%20994w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674562%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22221%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20Sansad%20TV%20screengrab%20of%20Ramesh%20Bidhuri.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20see%20the%20same%20glee%20when%20Muslims%20are%20lynched%20or%20tied%20to%20trees%20and%20compelled%20to%20chant%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJai%20Shree%20Ram%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(Hindutva%20slogan)%20on%20the%20faces%20of%20bystanders%20who%20take%20pictures%20of%20humiliation%20and%20violence%20on%20their%20phones.%20We%20saw%20the%20same%20excitement%20and%20clapping%20when%20a%20mob%20of%20men%20stripped%20two%20women%20and%20made%20them%20march%20naked%20in%20Manipur%2C%20while%20they%20openly%20molested%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESomething%20very%20ugly%20has%20been%20set%20off%20in%20our%20society.%20And%20this%20is%20a%20society%20that%20brandishes%20the%20platitude%20%E2%80%98the%20world%20is%20one%20family%E2%80%99%20as%20its%20unique%20contribution%20to%20world%20history.%20Let%20us%20make%20no%20mistake%2C%20silence%20or%20laughter%20at%20nauseating%20comments%20and%20violent%20acts%2C%20is%20acquiescence.%20One%20day%20future%20generations%20will%20ask%20why%20our%20generation%20was%20silent%20when%20this%20was%20happening%20in%20our%20country%2C%20the%20way%20the%20young%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20Germany%20ask%20their%20grandparents%20how%20they%20could%20be%20part%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98final%20solution%E2%80%99%20masterminded%20by%20Hitler.%20They%20ask%20these%20questions%20despite%20the%20rise%20of%20a%20right-wing%20neo-Nazi%20movement%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20question%20has%20perplexed%20many%20historians%20of%20modern%20Germany.%20On%20the%20basis%20of%20some%20hard%20work%20and%20time%20spent%20on%20perusing%20personal%20correspondence%20and%20diaries%2C%20historians%20tell%20us%20that%20not%20all%20Germans%20were%20active%20participants%20or%20supporters%20of%C2%A0%20the%20holocaust.%20Some%20were%20rankly%20sceptical%20of%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20project%20of%20creating%20a%20country%20free%20of%20the%20Jewish%20community%20but%20remained%20silent%2C%20and%20some%20approved%20of%20what%20was%20taking%20place%20before%20their%20eyes.%20The%20question%20of%20how%20Germans%20responded%20to%20the%20final%20solution%20is%20complex%20and%20complicated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20conditions%20imposed%20upon%20a%20defeated%20Germany%20after%20World%20War%20I%20by%20the%20victors%20created%20and%20sustained%20deep%20rooted%20grievances%2C%20and%20were%20a%20blow%20to%20national%20pride.%20This%20generated%20a%20strong%20sense%20of%20nationalism%20in%C2%A0%20most%20people.%20As%20the%20Germans%20were%20wracked%20by%20turmoil%20in%20the%20period%20between%20the%20two%20wars%2C%20a%20strong%20sense%20of%20victimhood%20loomed%20large%20over%20the%20country.%20Hitler%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20global%20power%20dominated%20by%20the%20Aryan%20race%20by%20conquering%20the%20Slav%20nations%20and%20exterminating%C2%A0%20the%20Jewish%20community%20by%20evoking%20disquiet%20and%20mortification%20coupled%20with%20the%20development%20of%20strong%20nationalism%20in%20the%20country.%20Many%20might%20not%20have%20supported%20the%20concentration%20camp%2C%20but%20they%20became%20silent%20spectators%20of%20the%20horror%20being%20inflicted%20on%20the%20Jewish%20community.%20Families%20broke%20up%20and%20friendships%20were%20sundered%20over%20the%20Nazi%20project.%20But%20national%20pride%2C%20survival%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20race%20as%20a%20marker%20of%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20nation%20absorbed%20the%20population%20to%20a%20large%20extent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-at-75-my-nationalism-jesuits%5C%22%3ENo%20Country%20for%20My%20Nationalism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20should%20learn%20the%20lessons%20that%20history%20teaches%20us.%20Once%20politicians%2C%C2%A0%20skilled%20in%20manipulating%20insecurity%20and%20national%20pride%2C%20organise%20the%20political%20community%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20identity%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20racial%20or%20religious%2C%20ethnic%20or%20linguistic%20%E2%80%93%20on%20selective%20remembrance%20of%20history%2C%20exaggerated%20grievances%20and%20rabid%20nationalism%2C%20societies%20seldom%20recover.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECynical%20politicians%20use%20these%20weapons%20to%20radicalise%20societies%20for%20their%20own%20ambitions%20and%20the%20pursuit%20of%20absolute%20power.%20Societies%20suffer%2C%20and%20this%20suffering%20does%20not%20heal%20easily.%20It%20might%20never%20heal.%20Hate%20becomes%20a%20part%20of%20personal%20and%20collective%20psyche%20as%20weak%20and%20unacknowledged%20sentiments%20get%20translated%20into%20strong%20passions.%20In%20India%2C%20hate%20speech%20and%20its%20supporters%20have%20acted%20as%20a%20trigger%20to%20translate%20unarticulated%20prejudices%20into%20violence.%20And%20this%20is%20justified%20in%20the%20name%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20destructive%C2%A0%20ideologies%20%E2%80%93nationalism%20and%20pseudo-histories.%20Nationalism%20that%20exploits%20the%20past%20and%C2%A0%20targets%20communities%20on%20this%20basis%20in%20the%20present%2C%20is%20terrible%20to%20behold.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F09%2FCWS8ddaU8AAJbJT.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20Hobsbawm.%20Credit%3A%20Twitter%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22404%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-175132%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22269%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EEric%20Hobsbawm.%20Credit%3A%20Twitter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBritish%20historian%20Donald%20Sassoon%20has%20edited%20and%20written%20a%20preface%20for%20a%20collection%20of%20essays%20by%20fellow%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Feric-hobsbawm-historian-lived-interesting-times%5C%22%3Ehistorian%20Eric%20Hobsbawm%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20Sassoon%2C%20Hobsbawm%20was%20fond%20of%20saying%20that%20there%20might%20have%20been%20a%20time%20he%20believed%20that%20historians%2C%20who%20fed%20into%20the%20nationalist%20project%2C%20unlike%20architects%20and%20civil%20engineers%20could%20not%20cause%20disasters.%20Hobsbawm%20eventually%20recognised%20that%20history%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20nationalists%20can%20kill%20more%20people%20than%20incompetent%20builders.%20%E2%80%9CHistory%20is%20the%20raw%20material%20for%20nationalist%20or%20ethnic%20or%20fundamentalist%20ideologies%2C%20as%20poppies%20are%20the%20raw%20material%20for%20heroin%20addicts%2C%20%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENationalism%20in%20the%20wrong%20hands%20can%20scar%20a%20nation.%20Politicians%20should%20be%20careful%20in%20evoking%20primordial%20passions%2C%20for%20the%20consequences%20for%20human%20societies%20are%20serious.%20The%20politicisation%20of%20religion%20or%20ethnicity%20leads%20to%20unimaginable%20tragedies.%20Some%20might%20participate%20in%20these%20tragedies%3B%20others%20might%20watch%2C%20but%20witnesses%20are%20by%20no%20means%20innocent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20issue%20of%20how%20we%20remember%20history%20came%20up%20sharply%20in%20the%20period%20that%20followed%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Berlin%20wall%20in%201989.%20The%201990s%20witnessed%20a%20series%20of%20ethno-nationalist%20wars%20that%20swamped%20the%20Balkans%20and%20then%20major%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20rise%20of%20fanatical%20nationalism%20based%20on%20selective%20historical%20memory%20that%20resulted%20in%20hate%20and%20massacres%2C%20motivated%20a%20number%20of%20scholars%20to%20try%20to%20understand%20the%20politics%20of%20selective%20remembrance%20or%20memory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20273px)%2085vw%2C%20273px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26134845%2FHabermas10_14298469242-220x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22273%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26134845%2FHabermas10_14298469242-220x300.jpg%20220w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26134845%2FHabermas10_14298469242-749x1024.jpg%20749w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26134845%2FHabermas10_14298469242.jpg%20878w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-676933%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22372%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJ%C3%BCrgen%20Habermas.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGerman%20philosopher%20Jurgen%20Habermas%2C%20who%20belongs%20to%20the%20tradition%20set%20by%20the%20inter-war%20Frankfurt%20School%20of%20Critical%20Theory%2C%20has%20written%20extensively%20on%20memory.%20Habermas%20uses%20the%20phrase%20collective%20memory%20to%20persuasively%20argue%20for%20dialogue%20and%20communication%20between%20contested%20world%20views.%20This%20is%20one%20way%20of%20recovering%20from%20the%20past%2C%20and%20learning%20from%20it.%20He%20searched%20for%20an%20expansive%20political%20community%20within%20which%20these%20debates%20are%20conducted%20to%20disable%20the%20devastating%20effects%20of%20nationalism.%20Accordingly%2C%20Habermas%20defends%20the%20need%20for%20post-national%20forms%20of%20political%20community%2C%20i.e.%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20so%20that%20the%20blood-spattered%20history%20of%20the%20nation%20can%20be%20transcended%2C%20and%20we%20are%20able%20to%20reach%20beyond%20the%20nation%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20scholars%20who%20subscribe%20to%20critical%20theory%20have%20struggled%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20memory.%20Max%20Horkheimer%2C%20one%20the%20most%20distinguished%20members%20of%20the%20school%2C%20had%20written%20that%20%E2%80%98past%20injustice%20has%20occurred%20and%20is%20completed.%20The%20slain%20are%20really%20slain%E2%80%99.%20The%20underlying%20conviction%20is%20that%20we%20cannot%20forget%20the%20past.%20To%20forget%20the%20past%20is%20to%20repress%20it%20in%20the%20Freudian%20sense.%20What%20is%20repressed%20will%20at%20some%20point%20or%20the%20other%20emerge%20as%20a%20sickness.%20What%20we%20can%20best%20do%20is%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20past%20to%20ensure%20that%20atrocities%20committed%20many%20centuries%20ago%20are%20not%20repeated%20in%20the%20present%20or%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20India%20however%2C%20we%20deal%20with%20another%20more%20troubling%20phenomenon%20%E2%80%93%20the%20legitimisation%20of%20state%20power%20through%20selective%20remembrance%20and%20hyper-nationalism.%20This%20does%20not%20let%20people%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20past%2C%20it%20pries%20open%20old%20wounds%2C%20targets%20minorities%2C%20and%20tries%20to%20build%20a%20nation%20through%20muscular%20and%20aggressive%20nationalism%20whether%20in%20the%20form%20of%20hate-speech%2Clynching%20of%20Muslims%2C%20or%20destruction%20of%20churches.%20A%20nation%20built%20on%20tolerance%20of%20hate%20speech%2C%20or%20open%20support%20for%20such%20speech%20as%20we%20saw%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20cannot%20but%20be%20scarred.%20For%20violence%20hurts%20not%20only%20the%20victim%20but%20the%20perpetrator.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Freal-patriotism-is-to-fight-nationalism-heres-why%5C%22%3EReal%20Patriotism%20Is%20to%20Fight%20Nationalism.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20Why.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20manipulation%20of%20a%20common%20past%20explodes%20on%20the%20consciousness%20of%20the%20people%2C%20and%20manufactures%20an%20enemy%20with%20whom%20there%20can%20be%20neither%20truck%20nor%20transaction.%20This%20is%20the%20tragedy%20of%20our%20times.%20The%20Urdu%20poet%20Bashir%20Badr%20wrote%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98dushmani%20jam%20kar%20karo%20lekin%20ye%20gunjaish%20rahe%20%2F%20jab%20kabhi%20hum%20dost%20ho%20jaaen%20to%20sharminda%20na%20hon%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(be%20my%20enemy%20with%20all%20the%20passion%20you%20command%2C%20but%20leave%20enough%20scope%2C%20for%20if%20we%20become%20friends%2C%20we%20should%20not%20be%20ashamed).%20In%20the%20language%20of%20political%20theory%3A%C2%A0%20no%20matter%20how%20deep%20the%20social%20divide%20is%2C%C2%A0%20there%20should%20be%20some%20space%20for%20reconciliation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20261px)%2085vw%2C%20261px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F26113407%2FA-Muslim-pilgrim-learns-a-lesson-in-piety-from-a-Brahman-from-a-Mughal-manuscript-of-one-of-Amir-Khusrows-poems-1-211x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%20this%20folio%20from%20a%20quintet%20by%20Amir%20Khusrow%2C%20a%20Muslim%20pilgrim%20learns%20a%20lesson%20in%20piety%20from%20a%20Brahman.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22261%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F26113407%2FA-Muslim-pilgrim-learns-a-lesson-in-piety-from-a-Brahman-from-a-Mughal-manuscript-of-one-of-Amir-Khusrows-poems-1-211x300.jpg%20211w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F26113407%2FA-Muslim-pilgrim-learns-a-lesson-in-piety-from-a-Brahman-from-a-Mughal-manuscript-of-one-of-Amir-Khusrows-poems-1-721x1024.jpg%20721w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F26113407%2FA-Muslim-pilgrim-learns-a-lesson-in-piety-from-a-Brahman-from-a-Mughal-manuscript-of-one-of-Amir-Khusrows-poems-1.jpg%20845w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-374714%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22371%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIn%20this%20folio%20from%20a%20quintet%20by%20Amir%20Khusro%2C%20a%20Muslim%20pilgrim%20learns%20a%20lesson%20in%20piety%20from%20a%20Brahman.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20project%20of%20reconciliation%2C%20or%20even%20leaving%20scope%20for%20future%20friendships%2C%20is%20difficult.%20The%20manoeuvring%20of%20historical%20memory%20has%20become%20a%20convenient%20weapon%20to%20hide%20mis-governance%2C%20hunger%20and%20poverty.%20The%20forcible%20exclusion%20of%20memories%20that%20tell%20stories%20of%20a%20culture%20of%20fusion%20in%20the%20mediaeval%20times%20%E2%80%93%20from%20classical%20Hindustani%20music%2C%20miniature%20Mughal%20paintings%2C%20magnificent%20Mughal%20architecture%2C%20to%20the%20way%20all%20communities%20worshipped%20at%20roadside%20shrines%20of%20Sufi%20saints%2C%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20beautiful%20common%20language%2CUrdu%2C%20to%20folk%20music%20of%20love%20and%20longing%2C%20to%20great%20works%20of%20literature%20and%20poetry%20%E2%80%93%20has%20torn%20apart%20communal%20solidarities.%20This%2C%20it%20is%20expected%2C%20will%20create%20fictional%20solidarity%20among%20the%20dominant%20community%3B%20a%20solidarity%20that%20is%20used%20for%20ignoble%20ends%20such%20as%20securing%20a%20majority%20in%20the%20next%20election.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Tagore%2C%20nationalism%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20pernicious%20exports%20of%20the%20West.%20He%20argued%20that%20nationalism%20is%20not%20a%20child%20of%20liberty%20or%20reason%20but%20the%C2%A0%20opposite%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20of%20fervent%20romanticism%20and%20the%20idea%20of%20political%20messiahs%20whose%20consequence%20is%20invariably%20the%20annihilation%20of%20freedom.%20He%20believed%20in%20a%20world%20that%20had%20not%20been%20broken%20up%20into%20fragments%20by%20narrow%20domestic%20walls.%20In%20his%20essay%20on%20nationalism%2C%20Tagore%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%98my%20countrymen%20will%20truly%20gain%20their%20India%20by%20fighting%20against%20the%20education%20which%20teaches%20them%20that%20a%20country%20is%20greater%20than%20the%20ideals%20of%20humanity%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFinally%2C%20it%20is%20a%20pity%20that%20the%20new%20building%20housing%20the%20Indian%20parliament%2C%20which%20should%20have%20been%20inaugurated%20by%20a%20renewed%20commitment%20to%20the%20Constitution%2C%20has%20been%20inaugurated%20by%20vulgar%20hate%20speech.%20It%20does%20not%20augur%20well%20for%20a%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%20or%20whatever%20is%20left%20of%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fneera-chandhoke%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ENeera%20Chandhoke%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20was%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Delhi%20University.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695724249000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26135717%2FF63GWclXkAAYn4S.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Ft